description: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. this pokémon’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.
Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.
When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves such as hypnosis and confusion.
This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. it seems to be closely related to wailmer.
The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.
It freely controls three small units called mini-noses using magnetic force.
It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. the flower flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.
This pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. it protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.
Slakoth lolls around for over twenty hours every day. because it moves so little, it does not need much food. this pokémon’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.
It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees f. what seems to be its body is actually hollow.
When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. the spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.
It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.
Known as “the being of knowledge.” it is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
This pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. it teams up with a tatsugiri to catch prey.
Thought to be one of the first pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.
Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. this pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. it stays motionless as it waits for evolution.
Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. it simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. this pokémon’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.
Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. it eats grass growing within its reach. if it eats all the grass it can reach, this pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.
Often mistaken for eggs. when disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.
Known as “the being of emotion.” it taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. for that reason, this pokémon was long believed to be invisible.
The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. these are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird pokémon, this pokémon is totally fine.
When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.
Known as “the being of willpower.” it sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. in victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.
When attacked, this pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. it’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.
It can tell how its trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. this empathic sense lets them run as if one being.
It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. this revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

Shedinja’s hard body doesn’t move - not even a twitch. in fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. it is believed that this pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.
Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this pokémon's real face.
Normally, Whismur’s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. however, if this pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.
Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this pokémon is 10 times stronger than girafarig’s.
When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. it runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.
Known for its extreme intelligence, this pokémon will look down on inexperienced trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran trainers.
Only a bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.
Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. if this pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it’s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.
It dwells in volcanic caves. it digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.
There is an enduring legend that states this pokémon towed continents with ropes.
While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.
This pokémon is a coward. as it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.
Makuhita is tenacious - it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. every time it gets back up, this pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.
Sightings of this pokémon have occurred in recent years. the name great tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.
Loudred’s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. it uses its voice to punish its foes. this pokémon’s round ears serve as loudspeakers.
Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. it leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.
With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.
Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. it is said to represent the crescent moon.
It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.
Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. the temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees fahrenheit.
Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.
It has the habit of challenging others without hesitation to tests of strength. it’s been known to stand on train tracks and stop trains using forearm thrusts.
Nosepass’s magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. if two of these pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.
A pokémon that lives by water. it moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.
It drifts in warm seas. it always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.
Possessed people controlled by this pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. as it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.
It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. this pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.
It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. it is active during nights of the new moon.
It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. this fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.
A pokémon with a one-track mind. once it charges,  it won't stop running until it falls asleep.
It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.
Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. because this pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.
Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. this pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.
To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.
It can distinguish the faintest of scents. it puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.
A rare and elusive pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.
It is described in mythology as the pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.
The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to sea­ weed. its vines shake as it walks.
It digs up the ground with its trunk. it’s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.
This pokémon brings victory. it is said that trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.
This pokémon has a body of steel. to make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.
Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.
It is very intelligent and calm. being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.
Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. this pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.
In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.
Capable of swim­ ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.
Two Binacle live together on one rock. when they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.
It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. it takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. it has a hard time walking around.
Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the water queen.
Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. however, whenever it meditates, this pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. as a result, its training never ends.
When they evolve, two binacle multiply into seven. they fight with the power of seven binacle.
Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.
It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. it roasts berries before it eats them.
In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.
When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. when in trouble, it emits smoke.
Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.
Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. this pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. these jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.
Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.
If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. the core flashes at midnight.
It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. it cares deeply about its friends.
Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. some people value the core as a gem.
They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.
After being reborn as a ghost pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.
It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. in response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.
Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.
Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. once this pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.
With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.
It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. it battles alongside dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.
When it isn’t battling, it keeps dreepy in the holes on its horns. once a fight starts, it launches the dreepy like supersonic missiles.

Dusclops’s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. it is said that its body is like a black hole. this pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.
It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. it can cause people to dance in unison with it.
They flare their frills and generate energy. a single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.
They make their home in deserts. they can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.
The bunches of fruit around Tropius’s neck are very popular with children. this pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. they use their tails to communicate with others.
This pokémon was restored from a fossil. if something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.
After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.
Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.
Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. for swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.
When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. it communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. this pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of illumise.
Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.
With its sweet aroma, it guides volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.
Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.
This ancient pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.
Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. the aroma of this pokémon brings serenity to living things.
It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.
It faces strong opponents with great courage. but, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent pokémon flees.
Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.
The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.
It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.
Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. the moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.
Virtually all of Gulpin’s body is its stomach. as a result, it can swallow something its own size. this pokémon’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.
It moves along the ground as if sliding. its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.
When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. once the prey has weakened, this pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.
It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like machamp and hariyama.
They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. their deceptively cute act is perfect.
Its whiskers serve as antennas. by sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.
These pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. many trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.
This pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. it’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the pokémon’s latent power.
Carvanha’s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. many boats have been attacked and sunk by this pokémon.
An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon pokémon. the theory remains unproven.
This pokémon dwells deep in the forest. eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.
Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. the leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.
Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.
Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. it’s also a belligerent pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.
Wailord is the largest of all identified pokémon up to now. this giant pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.
The weakest dragon-type pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.
It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.
Numel is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. however, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. this pokémon’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.
It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.
Lives close to water. its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.
When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° f. it uses its tuft to roast berries.
Wailmer’s nostrils are located above its eyes. this playful pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.
The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. the fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.
The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. plants that receive its water grow large.
These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.
You can tell how it’s feeling by the smoke spouting from its shell. tremendous velocity is a sign of good health.
When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.
A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. if one should chance upon this pokémon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.
The tuft on its head holds water. when the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.
Spoink bounces around on its tail. the shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. as a result, this pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it stops, its heart will stop.
These pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. they prefer to live in abandoned forests.
Munna always float in the air. people whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.
A pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. capable of moving freely in cyberspace.
It can control trees at will. it will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.
The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and pokémon.
Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. when this pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.
Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.
No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
A prehistoric pokémon that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.
Trapinch’s nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. this pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.
Each follows its trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.
Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname ”sea fiend.” it slurps up poison to nourish itself.
It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. it uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.
To make prey faint, Vibrava generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. this pokémon’s ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.
It can return to its trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.
A pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.
Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. the females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.
The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.
Its sleek shape is perfect for swim­ ming. it slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.
Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. this pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.
Flygon is nicknamed “the elemental  spirit of the desert.” because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.
They live in pitch-black caves. their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. it releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. when prey comes near, this pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.
They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.
This pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.
Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.
When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.
During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. this pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.
Legends say it can share eternal life. it slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.
This pokémon is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.
Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. this pokémon is not frightened of people. it lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.
The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the pokémon’s head.
When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.
When this legendary pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. the plant sprouts and grows with this pokémon.
It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. a hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.
The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.
Often found in forests, eating leaves. it has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.
Memories of battling its arch-rival seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose’s body. this pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.
Almost incapable of moving, this pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.
This pokémon migrated to paldea from distant lands long ago. the gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime."
By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. when angry, it rotates faster.
The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
Seviper shares a generations-long feud with zangoose. the scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. this pokémon attacks using its sword- edged tail.
These pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.
Long considered a mythical pokémon until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.
It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.
Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. as a result, some people theorize that this pokémon came from space. however, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.
It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. it’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.
Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. when it spins, its body shines.
A mystical pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. has the ability to change climate conditions.
It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. it could give a car running aboveground a good race.
This wary pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.
A common sight in forests and woods. it flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
An extremely rarely seen marine pokémon. its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. this pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.
Barboach’s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. this pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.
It searches for food all day. it possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.
It can help in tunnel construction. its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
Whiscash is extremely territorial. just one of these pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. if a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.
A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.
It has a very soft body. if it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.
Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. its pincers will never release prey.
It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. it is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.
So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. only a few people have seen it worldwide.
The shell seems to be filled with joy. it is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of scyther, this pokémon’s natural enemy.
While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. it sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.
Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this pokémon, making them desolate places.
It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. it takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.
When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
This pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.
A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. it is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.
The scent of spices comes from around its neck. somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.
At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. the bell rings brightly whenever this pokémon spits fire.
This pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. if it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.
It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. primitive wall paintings depicting this pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.
When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter showdown mode. it neutralizes its enemies in short order.
It has its third set of legs folded up. when it’s in a tough spot, this pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.
The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. this pokémon moves about while levitating.
They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.
This pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. it’s famous for being a hard worker.
A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.
It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. these sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.
When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.
When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.
It controls its water balloons with song. the melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. this ancient pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.
Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. this pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.
They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. they use vibration to hurt their opponents.
Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. this primitive pokémon once lived in warm seas. it grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.
This pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.
Armaldo’s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. this pokémon’s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. they have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.
Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.
Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. even its trainer must be careful.
It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. when it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.
The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.
Feebas’s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. because of its shoddy appearance, this pokémon is largely ignored. it is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.
Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. they change color depending on the viewing angle.
Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. it hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.
When it battles, its beak heats up. the temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.
If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. there are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. it did not originally live in alola but was imported from another region.
This pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the pokémon’s vicinity.
Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
Upon finding a small pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.
